OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1777731064
OL,3,CFormer Chief Minister resigns from top
OL,4,Ccommittee after arrest
OL,6,FIn response to Deputy St Pier's
OL,7,Fresignation from P&R, committee
OL,8,Fpresident, Deputy Lindsay de Sausmarez
OL,9,Fsaid: "We, the other members of the
OL,10,FPolicy & Resources Committee, met to
OL,11,Fdiscuss the situation and ` whilst
OL,12,Fbeing clear that this confers no
OL,13,Fcommentary on Deputy St. Pier's guilt
OL,14,F` agreed that the most appropriate
OL,15,Fcourse of action would be for Deputy
OL,16,FSt. Pier to offer his resignation.
OL,18,F"I did not have to ask him to do so,
OL,19,Fhowever, as he told me of his decision
OL,20,Fin a conversation this morning."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/8
